  "conclusion": "c4 native batch full-attention O-output is not intrinsically red: rowchunk3 with native batch O-output preserves generated-token equality [137,137,137,137]. However c4 full-native/no-chunk native batch output remains red [137,137,137,118], c4 rowchunk3 with batch_gemv output is red [82,137,137,137], and c8 rowchunk3 is red for both output modes. The output-path bug is coupled to row-chunk partitioning and row count; this is correctness evidence only and does not replace the c4/c8 rowchunk2 batch_gemv default or unblock retained throughput.",
